The Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party, (PDP), Plateau State Chapter, Hon. Chris Hassan has said the victory of the party in the March 18 governorship election of Barr. Caleb Mutfwang and State Assembly lie squarely on the shoulders of youthful eligible Plateau voters. He stated this yesterday in his office while hosting Youths from Tudun Wada and a forum of councilors from Bassa who paid him a congratulatory visit. The government of Caleb Mutfwang will focus on youth and women’s inclusiveness to improve the party’s fortunes in the future. He explained that young people in the state play pivotal roles in Winning elections and the party leadership will extend their hand of fellowship to them. He stressed “the time is now” for Plateau people to experience a dividend of democracy directly and positively. For eight years, darkest hovered the land, the people held bondage with no leader but today, the land is green, the iron gates are broken, light has come to Plateau State and we have begun our journey to promise land, Barr. Caleb Mutfwang is the leader. Rejoice oh land for your leader has emerged, the leader that looks like you.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒ You are not going to just work for the party but you are going to be there to make sure that the government of Barr. Caleb Mutfwang works functionally and effectively. POLL He thanked the youths of Tudun wada, the plateau youths and forum of councilors in Bassa and assured them their sacrifices will not be in vain. The youth leader of Tudun wada, Richard God-knows and forum of councilors in Bassa, Hon samuel tembau all in their separate remarks congratulated the Governor-elect, Barr Caleb Mutfwang, members of National & State Assembly and wish them Godspeed.